FBIS4-48563 "drafr099_d_94022" FBIS-AFR-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Malawi Aford on Harassment; Chihana To Meet Muluzi Aford on Harassment; Chihana To Meet Muluzi MB2105180794 Blantyre Malawi Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 1600 GMT 21 May 94 MB2105180794 Blantyre Malawi Broadcasting Corporation Network English BFN [Text] The Alliance for Democracy, Aford, has complained that its members are being harassed and beaten by supporters of the United Democratic Front, UDF, in some parts of Blantyre, following's UDF's election victory. A statement by Aford Organizing Secretary [name indistinct] said the incidents happened in [words indistinct] and that they have been reported to the police. He appealed to UDF supporters to [words indistinct]. In Karonga, the president of the Alliance for Democracy, Aford, Mr. Chakufwa Chihana, has called on his supporters in the district to refrain from any violence. Speaking when he addressed his supporters to brief them on election results, Mr. Chihana said the fact that they have lost the election should be no (?guarantee) to quarrel with members of other parties, especially the UDF. He said in the new Malawi there is need to live together. Mr. Chihana also told the people that he is due to hold discussions with the state president on the issue of running the government.
